# Commands: repo root and Nx

- Run workspace tooling from the **repository root** (`source`). Do not document or suggest `cd` into `apps/*` or `libs/*` to run package `npm run` scripts as an alternate path.
- **Nx is the only invoker** for package targets: `npx nx run <project>:<target>` and `npx nx run-many -t <target> --all`, including any trailing root-only steps already chained in those flows (for example `npx biome check` / `npx biome format` on root config files after `run-many -t lint` / `format`).
- Do not add root `package.json` scripts that only duplicate an equivalent `npx nx run …` with no extra behavior.
- **Exception:** `npm install` (and `npm ci` in CI) runs only at the repo root; there is no Nx substitute.
